description: "The amendment in the IT Intermediary Rules, which has been stayed by SC, that is still under contest... but fundamental principle is, our point is, anything related to the government of India, only the government can say whether it is a correct fact or a wrong fact. Candidates can check the detailed schedule on the NTA website and download admit cards a few days before the exam. Contact NTA for further details.
title: UGC NET 2024: NTA releases rescheduled exam timetable, details here

description: Nitin Gadkari announced that the Delhi-Mumbai Expressway project is now expected to be completed by October 2025, with 82% of the construction already finished. Currently, 630 km are accessible, and the full Sohna-Vadodara stretch may be open by March 2025, significantly reducing travel time between the two cities.
title: When will Delhi-Mumbai Expressway project be completed?

description: OpenAI launched a new advanced voice mode for ChatGPT Plus users, featuring real-time responses and emotional engagement. Shark Tank judge Anupam Mittal compared it to Amazon Alexa's initial promise, noting Alexa's decline in use. He highlighted the current perception of AI as a novelty, but acknowledged its potential for future practicality.
title: Shark Tank judge Anupam Mittal has this 'Amazon Alexa reminder' for 'ChatGPT-AI hype'

description: The body of 14-year-old Shivam Kumar was discovered in an orchard in Begusarai district, with his private part mutilated and a rope around his neck. Allegations suggest the local mukhiya is involved due to a land dispute. Police are investigating and conducting raids to apprehend suspects. Further forensic analysis is underway.
title: In Bihar, Class 8 student strangled, private part missing
'How can someone compare Indian budget to 'Halwa': Kangana Ranaut

description: Congress mocked Prime Minister Narendra Modi after reports of water leakage in the new Parliament building following heavy rains in Delhi. They posted an animated video and highlighted the issue of weather resilience. The Lok Sabha secretariat explained that the leak was due to minor adhesive displacement in securing glass domes above the lobby.
title: Watch: Congress mocks PM Modi over water leakage in new Parliament

description: In late July, 12 inmates died at Asha Kiran, Delhi's government-run mental health facility, sparking concerns over neglect and poor conditions. Most victims exhibited symptoms of loose motions and vomiting. Investigations are underway to check for water contamination or food poisoning, amidst previous reports highlighting longstanding issues in the overcrowded and understaffed shelter.
title: Deaths at Delhi govt’s shelter home spike in July, spark alarm

description: Bhavana Sajin, a mother from Idukki known for her charity in breastfeeding orphaned newborns, experienced a disheartening situation. After receiving calls about an urgent need for breast milk at relief camps, she and her husband Sajin Parekkara traveled 350km to Wayanad. However, upon arrival, the contacts who had reached out to them were unresponsive. The couple visited the relief camp at Meppadi Government School and nearby hospitals but found no baby in need. They are currently staying with relatives in Sultan Bathery.
title: Wayanad tragedy: Woman offers to breastfeed orphans, tricked
Telangana NRI rigged H-1B visa lottery system, claims report

description: An intellectually challenged 14-year-old boy in Kalyan unknowingly spent four days with his deceased mother's body due to her sudden illness. Neighbours, alerted by a foul smell, discovered the situation. The incident highlights societal alienation. The police confirmed no foul play, and the body was handed to her family after a post-mortem examination.
title: Boy sits next to dead mom for four days in Maharashtra's Kalyan

description: A first-year MBBS student was arrested for allegedly pushing his classmate from a third-floor balcony, resulting in her death. Both 21-year-olds studied at a medical college near Karad. The deceased, Arushi Mishra, had reportedly been troubled by Dhruv Chikkara, the accused. Police investigations continue as he faces murder charges.
title: Maharashtra: Pushed by classmate from 3rd floor, MBBS student dies
UP transfers DCP, ADCP, ACP for ‘letting off’ Lucknow molesters
